24:
Now I rejoice in my sufferings
 for you, and I am completing in my flesh what is lacking in Christ’s afflictions for his body,
 that is, the church.

1:
For I want you to know how greatly I am struggling
 for you, for those in Laodicea,
 and for all who have not seen me in person.

3:
At the same time, pray also for us that God may open a door
 to us for the word, to speak the mystery of Christ,
 for which I am in chains,

13:
For I testify about him that he works hard
 for you, for those in Laodicea,
 and for those in Hierapolis.
